com.wm.xmldata

Class XmlDataGroupTag

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wm.xmldata.XmlDataTag
      • com.wm.xmldata.XmlDataContentTag
        • com.wm.xmldata.XmlDataGroupTag
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class XmlDataGroupTag
extends XmlDataContentTag
    The XmlDataGroupTag class constructs an XmlData group-tag from its constituent parts. There are methods that return the full-name as well as the path-name. The full-name is used in XmlData infosets. The path-name is used in map-paths and copy-paths; they contains additional qualifying information. In an XmlData infoset, group-tags are always paired with group-values and the pair is contained in another group-value.

    The group-tag full-name format is: 

    {particle-id}*group
    where the particle-id identifies the position of this group relative to all groups in a content model. A group-tag is created for each sequence, choice, or all group in the schema content model from which a Document Type is created.

    Consider the schema content model: 

    
    <sequence>
       <element name="abc" />
       <any/>
       <choice> ... </choice>
    </sequence>
       
    results in a Document type with fields:
    
         {1}abc#target
         {1}*any
         {1}*group

    The group-tag path-name format provides an additional property, index: 

         {particle-id}*group[index]
    where index is either a non-negative integer. For a copy-pth it may also be an index-iterator.
